      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Thiamin diphosphate (TPP), a derivative of vitamin B<sub>1</sub> required for glucose metabolism, is a weak acid that can be deprotonated by a base. Assign formal charges to the appropriate atoms in both TPP and its deprotonation product.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcHNRIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--b327915688994d191c769c9208fc0ddb911a42c6/OChem_02_EC_028.jpg\" alt=\"Thiamin diphosphate reacts with base forming a product, in which the hydrogen (with p K a 18) at C2 of the 5-membered ring is replaced with a lone pair.\">",
